Working from home? Here’s a great tip in case you need to scan a document. iPhone users: go to “notes” and hit the little camera button. It will ask if you want to scan a document. Lay out the pages you want to scan and it will save them all as a PDF file! So easy and helpful if you depend on using a scanner like I do!

Feel free to add any more helpful hints for those working from home.

Putnam County Health Department
March 6 at 4:50 PM ·

Ohio Department of Health (ODH) has opened a call center to help answer questions regarding coronavirus (COVID-19). The call center will be open 7 days a week from 9:00 a.m. to 8:00 p.m. and can be reached at 1-833-4-ASK-ODH (1-833-427-5634).
Call center staff includes licensed nurses and infectious disease experts. They will be available to answer questions and provide accurate information about COVID-19, the risk to the public, and the state’s response.
There are still no confirmed cases of COVID-19 in Ohio at this time, however it is still very important to use precautions to help prevent the disease.

post_text:
The National Honor Society is proud to sponsor Ottoville school’s next blood drive with the American Red Cross on October 30.

An estimated 38 percent of Americans are eligible to give blood or platelets, but of those, less than 10 percent actually donate each year. If you are healthy and eligible, please come out to donate. Most donations take about an hour, so book your appointment, roll up your sleeve and become a part of the lifesaving mission of the Red Cross and NHS. To donate you must be healthy and feel well the day of the donation, be 17 or 16 years old with parental consent, and weigh at least 110 pounds (additional weight requirements for high school students redcrossblood.org). Be sure to bring a photo id.

Donation times are from 7:00 am to 1:00 pm. To sign up email sjones@ottovilleschools.org or call the high school at 419-453-3358. All donations are appreciated!

shared_text:
Kent Tarbox is with Ruth Miller.
March 5, 2017 at 10:09 AM ·

Just had to post this picture from a game I covered on Saturday. These women are all grandmothers of girls that play basketball for Ottoville. These women were fun to talk to and were all in with their support of Ottoville.

High school sports are competitive and sometimes the event brings out the worst in fans and unfortunately that is what we see and usually remember once the event is over. So that being said, I wanted to take a moment and recognize the more positive side of high school athletic competitions.

Every school has their supporters that are at every event during good seasons and bad, good weather and foul and at the end of the game they recognize the efforts put forth by both teams and represent their communities in a positive manner. These are the fans I want to give a shout out too and say Thank you for being the fan and supporter we should all strive to be... hats off to you ladies....

Ottoville Big Green Yearbook
October 10, 2016 at 1:58 PM ·

We've received positive response from uploading last year's yearbook pictures to the ReplayIt App. We are starting to load more photos for this year's sports and activities. However, the purpose of the app is for you, the parents and community members, to upload your good photos to the app, so we can include them in the yearbook. Please help add to these collections by downloading the app on your device and sharing your photos of Ottoville school athletes, fans, and school activities.

shared_text:
Ottoville Lady Green Volleyball
October 20, 2016 at 8:11 PM ·

Your Lady Green Are 2016 SECTIONAL CHAMPS! They beat Delphos St. John's in 4 tonight!

Leading the Lady Green were:
CJ Kemper: 13 kills, 12 digs, 2 aces
Bridget Landin: 9 kills, 13 blocks, 12 digs
Quinley Schlagbaum: 9 kills, 9 digs
Alexis Thorbahn: 22 assists, 9 blocks
Brynnlee Hanneman: 10 blocks

The Lady Green advance to 19-4 and move on to District Semi-Finals Tuesday at Van Wert. They will take on New Bremen with play beginning at 6:00! Come out and support your Lady Green as they push forward in tournament! 💚💛🏐
